On Sun, 1 Sep 2002, Ian Janes wrote:

>
>
> Well yesterday I was at my local junkyard and I came a cross someones old
> drag bug,
> the motor and tranny still there! and they look way to
> clean ,there is oil in it and it looks like it was just changed too, the
> motor doesn't have the cooling shroud or a alt mount(its blocked off with a
> chrome plate). I can turn it over buy hand , the owner of the yard says the
> old owner says it runs. My question is what are some thing I should look for
> that might cause some problem .

If it's a drag motor it will be assembled to specs that will make it a
very poor engine for a bus.  Drag engines are designed to make a few
quarter-mile passes at maximum power, so they tend to run large
clearances.  Not what you want in a long-lived street engine.

